I'll build out the full study-tracker SaaS: a public landing page,              
email/password auth (Supabase-backed when configured, a signed-cookie session   
with hashed passwords otherwise), a protected dashboard with weekly stats and a 
create/list/delete flow for study sessions, and an API that requires auth and   
scopes every read/write to the current user (RLS-ready when Supabase is         
configured).                                                                    

Plan:                                                                           

 1 Add small lib/ modules: config (Supabase env detection), types, in-memory    
   user store (hashed passwords via Node's built-in crypto.scrypt), signed      
   session cookie (HMAC via crypto), and a unified getCurrentUser() that works  
   in either mode.                                                              
 2 Rewrite app/api/auth/route.ts — signup/login/logout, Supabase Auth REST calls
   when configured, otherwise the in-memory store + signed cookie. Fails closed 
   on bad input (400) and bad credentials (401).                                
 3 Rewrite app/api/items/route.ts — GET/POST/DELETE for study sessions, requires
   auth (401 otherwise), uses Supabase PostgREST with the user's own access     
   token (so RLS on auth.uid() enforces isolation) or an in-memory Map scoped by
   userId when unconfigured.                                                    
 4 Rewrite app/login/page.tsx — a real signup/login form.                       
 5 Rewrite app/dashboard/page.tsx (server component, redirects to /login when   
   signed out) + new app/dashboard/dashboard-client.tsx (the actual polished UI:
   weekly bar chart, log-session form, session list with delete,                
   loading/empty/error states).                                                 
 6 Rewrite app/page.tsx — a real marketing landing page (redirects to /dashboard
   if already signed in).                                                       

Note on Supabase mode: if you set SUPABASE_URL + SUPABASE_ANON_KEY, you need a  
study_sessions table with RLS enabled and policies keyed on auth.uid() = user_id
(columns: id uuid default gen_random_uuid() primary key, user_id uuid not null  
default auth.uid(), subject text, duration_minutes int, studied_at date,        
created_at timestamptz default now()). No npm packages required — I call        
Supabase's REST/Auth HTTP APIs directly with fetch, so the build never depends  
on an SDK that may not be installed.                                            

